The paper deals with the problem of secret key agreement, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The presence of an eavesdropper and the need for secrecy suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of channel state information and the consideration of a wiretap channel suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY), multimedia (cs.MM), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
